# Vercel JavaScript Micro-Optimizations

- **Set/Map**: Use for O(1) lookups instead of `array.find()` in loops
- **Index maps**: Build `Map` for repeated lookups; avoid repeated linear scans
- **Combine iterations**: Merge multiple `filter`/`map` passes into one loop
- **Cache**: Hoist RegExp outside loops; cache `localStorage`/`sessionStorage` reads; cache function results in module-level Map
- **Early exit**: Return early from functions; check array length before expensive comparisons
- **Min/max**: Use loop instead of `sort()` for finding min/max
- **Immutability**: Use `toSorted()` instead of `sort()` to avoid mutating
- **DOM/CSS**: Batch CSS changes via classes or `cssText`; cache object properties in loops
